subSubSection.paragraph:
Genitalia (
Fig. 27a–b
). Typical for the genus; crista sacculi of valva without distal ridge, recurved part rather broad, rather densely covered with long setae; vesica with simple sclerotized plate.

Genitalia (
Figs 28a–b
).Antrum funnel-shaped; ductus bursae more than twice the length of antrum; longitudinal fold three quarter the length of corpus bursae, signum slightly rhombic.
